raw.fdescription79869: John, Abraham, Joseph and Isaac Bowman were Virginia militia officers in the American Revolutionary War. They were legends, admired and respected by fellow settlers for their courage and bravery. This hand-crafted bourbon whiskey is a tribute to these four heroic Bowman Brothers. This small batch bourbon has been distilled three times using the finest corn, rye and malted barley. A. Smith Bowman's unique copper still produces a flavor like no other bourbon. After many years of aging in new charred oak barrels, this 90 proof Virginia bourbon whiskey will please even those with the most discerning tastes. The nose is warm like the Virginia summer. Its complex flavor has hints of vanilla and oak, while the finish is smooth and mellow like a quiet night on the front porch. Enjoy straight, over ice or with a splash of water.

raw.fdescription79869: Reservoir Bourbon is a one-of-a-kind, 100 percent corn mash bill, with a big, bright profile. Though most bourbons add a rye component to the mash bill for additional flavor—or, to a lesser extent, wheat—Reservoir trusts the full force of local Virginia corn and deep aging in small barrels to produce a unique bourbon that is different from any other product available on the market. Reservoir Bourbon is the most traditional yet unique whiskey in the Reservoir house expressions. It’s a beautiful midpoint balance of sweet between the softness of the Wheat and the sharp grain of the rye. Appealing to experienced whiskey hunters and the novice alike.

raw.fdescription79869: Murlarkey Justice White Whiskey begins with a bright, clean taste of fresh cut hay and farm milled sweet corn then slowly rounds into a full-bodied elixir touting herbal esters and a long soft finish. Justice is an ultra-pure whiskey, handcrafted from a proprietary blend of the finest Virginia corn and barley available. Locally milled and distilled in Bristow Virginia, Justice delivers a new category of corn-based spirits. Un-aged and with no additives, you will taste the clean, bright floral characteristics of fresh corn and the local Virginia terroir. Taste the whiskey that has been produced to honor the heritage of Virginia.

raw.fdescription79869: Reservoir Distillery's wheat whiskey is the softest of their three expressions. Wheat produces a buttery, savory and smooth whiskey, and is an excellent introductory whiskey for those not experienced in brown spirits. Some refer to it as a beginner bourbon. If you love the smoothness of a wheated bourbon you will fall in love with this 100 percent wheat mash bill. We recommend trying Reservoir Wheat Whiskey neat to establish a baseline, then adding a touch of water or a single ice cube to temper the proof.

raw.fdescription79869: A small batch bourbon produced by KO Distilling, a craft distillery located in historic Manassas. The spirit is a “wheated” bourbon made with 70 percent corn, 20 percent wheat and 10 percent malted barley, all sourced from local Virginia farms. At KO, the grains were milled, mashed, fermented and double-distilled, then placed in charred new American Oak barrels and aged on-site for at least 2 years. The bourbon was proofed at 90 and then bottled by hand. It is deliciously smooth, with notes of vanilla, caramel and the oak itself. Bare Knuckle Straight Bourbon Whiskey is a certified Virginia’s Finest product.

Brewers Batch was aged for 12 months in casks sourced from local breweries like Three Notch'd Brewing. This inaugural batch has a rich malty caramel note which accentuates the vanilla notes found in the originating whisky cask.

raw.fdescription79869: A remarkable rye whisky made with an extraordinarily generous amount of smoked malt. The mash bill is 2/3 Virginia rye and 1/3 Virginia thoroughbred hand-malted barley, kiln dried with apple wood and cherry wood smoke. Double pot-stilled to between 150 and 160 proof and aged with a progressive series of new and used apple wood and oak chips inside used bourbon barrels. Copper Fox Distillery's innovative aging process results in a truly unique rye whisky that is savory and complex with the characteristic Wasmund's finish.

This creates a refreshing taste with sweet upfront flavor from the wheat and a peppery finish from the rye.  Bare Knuckle American Whiskey may be enjoyed neat, on the rocks or in a variety of craft cocktails. It can be used in both traditional and non-traditional whiskey drinks alike.

raw.fpagez32xheading79869: Copper Fox Original Single Malt Whisky
raw.fdescription79869: Copper Fox Distillery in Sperryville use local fruitwoods to gently smoke and dry the grains in their spirits. Their single malt whisky has complex aromas of ripe stone fruit, cinnamon pastry and campfire smoke, with a syrupy, yet slightly drying body that is sweet and earthy at the same time. Flavors of marzipan, clove, orange zest and smoke give way to a medium-long finish with notes of dried fruit, honey and toasted oak. Recommended for sipping but unique cocktail possibilities abound.

raw.fpagez32xheading79869: Copper Fox Peachwood American Single Malt
raw.fdescription79869: Copper Fox Distillery is the only distillery in North America to hand malt their own barley, and the only distillery in the world using apple and cherry wood smoke to flavor the malted barley. Their single batch copper pot still produces one barrel at a time, and the spirit is non-chill filtered to preserve the complete flavor and essence of the barley grain. With flavors of suede, olive tapenade, honey, dried fruit chutney and clay, this Virginian whiskey is a medium-full body with a root beer float-like finish.

raw.fdescription79869: This whisky from Virginia Distillery Co. is made from 100% malted barley, marrying American Single Malt whisky made on site in Virginia with aged malt whisky from Scotland. Cask finishing for an additional 8 to 12 months in premium Cuvée red wine casks that have been re-toasted deepens the nuance and complexity of each single cask. Notes of raspberry, mocha and baking spice showcase the hallmarks of this cask type, sourced exclusively for Virginia Distillery Company's whiskies. $1 of each bottle sale will be donated to the veterans organization, Hope For The Warriors, which supports service members and their families after tours of duty.

The whisky is then cask finished for an average of 12 months in finishing casks sourced primarily from Virginia wineries. raw.fdescription79869: John, Abraham, Joseph and Isaac Bowman were Virginia militia officers in the American Revolutionary War. This hand-crafted bourbon whiskey is a tribute to these heroic Brothers. This small batch bourbon has been distilled three times using the finest corn, rye and malted barley. A. Smith Bowman's unique copper still produces a flavor like no other. After aging in new charred oak barrels, this Virginia bourbon whiskey will please even those with the most discerning tastes. The nose is warm an its complex flavor has hints of vanilla and oak. The finish is smooth and mellow. Enjoy straight, over ice or with a splash of water.

raw.fdescription79869: Distilled and bottled by Dome & Spear Distillery located in Evington, Virginia, this artisanal bourbon style whiskey is hand-crafted in small batches.  Established by the McCauley family in 2014, this is the first licensed distillery in Campbell County and named after the old wrought iron “dome and spear” fencing that surrounds many historic buildings in the area. Using locally grown Virginia corn, other US grains their family >recipe, each batch is distilled twice barreled and aged in new charred oak barrels.
